data.protoText: Dilute 1.666 µL of Proteinase K into 250 µL of 2X T and C Lysis Solution for each sample
Transfer 250 µL of the fluid sample to an O ring tube (prefi lled with beads)
250 µL of 2X T and C Lysis Solution containing the Proteinase K
Bead-beating lysis for 5 min (no more than 12 tubes each time)
Incubate at 65°C for 25 minutes in ThermoMixer; vortex every 5 minutes; set the shaking speed at 300 rpm
Centrifuge the tubes at 12,000 x g for 3 min at room temperature
Transfer 350+10 µL supernatant to a new microcentrifuge tube
Cool the samples to 37°C
add 1.666 µL of 5 mg/mL RNase A to the sample. Mix thoroughly
Incubate at 37°C for 50 minutes, still shaking at 300 rpm
Place the samples on ice for 5-8 minutes and then proceed with total DNA precipitation
Add 330 µL of MPC Protein Precipitation Reagent to lysed sample and vortex vigorously for 10 seconds.
Pellet the debris by centrifugation at 4°C for 18 minutes at 16,000 x g in a microcentrifuge.

Transfer the supernatant to a clean microcentrifuge tube and discard the pellet. Use different pipettes (1000 µL + 20 µL) to slowly and gently suction the maximum possible volume while maintaining the pellet intact.
Add 834 µL of isopropanol to the recovered supernatant. Invert the tube 50-60 times.
Pellet the DNA by centrifugation (16,000 x g) at 4°C for 18 minutes in a microcentrifuge
Carefully remove the isopropanol without dislodging the DNA pellet, using a pipette.
Rinse twice with fresh 70% ethanol.
Centrifuge briefly in between each washing step (2 min; 16,000 x g). Remove all of the residual ethanol with a pipette
Vacuum centrifuge the sample at room temperature for 2 min under V-AQ mode. The indicator is that the DNA pellet turns from white to transparent.
Resuspend the DNA in 50 µL of DNase-free water. Disrupt the DNA pellet gently by gently flicking the tube.
If necessary, leave the DNA at 4 °C overnight to rehydrate
